**************************************************************************************************** TIME COMPLEXITY **********************************************************************************************************
Time Complexity: O(n)

We traverse the input string of length nonce to group consecutive identical characters →O(n).`

We traverse the grouped characters once to build the compressed string → O(n) in total output length.

Each comparison and update operation takes constant time.

In total: O(n + n) = O(n).

Space Complexity: O(n)  

We store character–count pairs for each group of consecutive characters → O(g) where g ≤ n.

The compressed string can take up to O(n) space in the worst case (all characters unique).

Hence, the overall space complexity is O(n).
